# .dockerignore -- repo-root build-context filter for the two Docker-isolated
# auto-classifier-pilot test images.
#
# Both test compose files set `context: ../../..` (the REPO ROOT):
#   - tests/integration/auto-gate-live-http/docker-compose.yml (tester service)
#   - tests/e2e/auto-gate-classifier/docker-compose.yml (e2e-runner service)
#
# Without this file, the ENTIRE repo tree ships into the build context on every
# `docker compose ... build`. That is both bloat (.git, tmp, rendered state) and
# a leak surface. This file keeps the context to exactly what the two
# Dockerfiles COPY, and EXCLUDES leak-sensitive paths — most importantly refs/,
# which holds a local reference bundle containing third-party
# product names that must NEVER enter an image layer.
#
# The two Dockerfiles' COPY surface (what this file MUST keep reachable):
#   Dockerfile.tester (integration):
#     - .vh-agent-harness/overlays/auto-classifier-pilot/plugins/*.js (3 files)
#     - templates/sys-prompts/auto-gate-classifier.md
#     - tests/integration/auto-gate-live-http/auto-gate-live-http.test.mjs
#   Dockerfile.e2e-runner (e2e):
#     - Stage 1: `COPY . .` then `go build ./cmd/vh-agent-harness`
#       (needs cmd/, internal/, corpus.go, core_manifest.go, go.mod, go.sum,
#        templates/ for go:embed) + render (.vh-agent-harness/ overlay pack +
#        tests/e2e/auto-gate-classifier/vh-harness-profile.yml)
#     - Stage 2: tests/e2e/auto-gate-classifier/e2e-driver.mjs
#
# NOTE: the mock-llm services build with `context: .` (their own test dir), so
# this repo-root file does NOT affect them.

# --- VCS + build artifacts (bloat) ---
.git/
.gitignore
tmp/

# --- Rendered state (regenerated inside containers; never needed in context) ---
.opencode/

# --- Operator-private overlay state ---
.local/

# --- Node deps (none in this repo, but exclude defensively if ever added) ---
node_modules/

# --- LEAK-PREVENTION: reference bundle with third-party product names ---
# refs/ holds a local reference bundle. It must NEVER ship into a
# Docker image layer. Excluding it here is both bloat reduction and a hard
# leak-prevention guard at the image-build boundary.
refs/

# --- Operator-private research docs (gitignored locally; never in images) ---
*.local.md
researches/sources/*.local.md

# --- Editor / OS cruft ---
.DS_Store
*.swp
*.swo
*~
.idea/
.vscode/

# --- This file itself is not needed in the image (harmless, but keep it out) ---
.dockerignore
